# ☀️ Solar Potential Map for Off-Grid Kenya

## The Problem
Over 30% of Kenyans have no access to the national grid. Solar energy
is the most viable solution for off-grid communities — but where should
NGOs, investors and installers prioritize?

## What This Project Does
- Fetches real solar irradiance data from Open-Meteo API for all 47 counties
- Builds a solar suitability scoring model based on radiation and consistency
- Ranks all 47 counties into 3 priority tiers
- Visualizes results on an actual Kenya map using GeoPandas
- Provides an interactive MVP for NGO deployment planning

## Tools Used
- Python
- Pandas — data processing
- Requests — API calls
- GeoPandas — geospatial mapping
- Matplotlib & Seaborn — visualizations
- Open-Meteo API — free solar radiation data

## How To Run

### Fetch fresh data
```bash
python fetch_solar_data.py
```

### Run the interactive app
```bash
python app.py
```

### Open the analysis notebook
```bash
jupyter notebook notebooks/analysis.ipynb
```

## Key Findings
- Top county: Uasin Gishu (83.3/100)
- Lowest county: Kwale (7.4/100)
- Tier 1 counties: Uasin Gishu, Turkana, Baringo, Elgeyo Marakwet, Nakuru, Kisumu
- Best region: Rift Valley
- Worst region: Coast (high humidity reduces irradiance)

## Data Source
Open-Meteo Historical Weather API — free, no API key required
Kenya County Boundaries — GADM v4.1